snippet.textDisplay:
For those who want to know what he is saying, 

He is basically saying that the shoreline is always quiet and peaceful and safe, but humans are not made for that, the true 'Khalasi' means a person who dives in the ocean for pearls, a true Khalasi is the one who goes into the dangerous ocean looking for pearls.

If you want a line-by-line translation, pls tell me in the comments

Edit: After so many people asking, let's go!
I will start the translation from the rap itself

Kinare to kalhi padi nani ......-This line means that on the coastline, only small footprints can be made- which then means that you can only achieve small things while stitting at the coastline

Line 2 basically emphasizes the meaning of the first line

The next few lines mean to say that even in dangerous situations, The true khalasi, will go into the depts of the ocean to find pearls to earn a living- in it's literary form this line is trying to say that, only the people with the guts to take the risk to do something dengerous, are the ones who end begin the most successful.


I have tried my best to explain the literary point of view of the sang, please tell me if I can imporve
